==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hawker
<hw>Hawk"er</hw> <pr>(h⟦add⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who
sells wares by crying them in the street; hence, a peddler or a
packman.</def> <rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hawker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hawker
<hw>Hawk"er</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To sell goods by outcry in the
street.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Hudibras.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hawker</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hawker
<hw>Hawk"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS. <ets>hafecere</ets>. See
1st <er>Hawk</er>.]</ety> <def>A falconer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hawkey</ent>⟦br⟧
